724225f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - 13th Street
724225f-a.text:
Washington Street, west side, north from clearing adjoining and at
the S.W. corner of 13th Street. These last two blocks of Washington
Street, which are parallel to Ninth Avenue, vere only cut through
from Little West 12th to 14th Streets about 1890, probably to
expedite traffic bound for the new West Washington Market, between
West Strect and Thirteenth avenue.
July 28, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

724226f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - 13th Street
724226f-a.text:
Washington Street, west side, from 13th to Little West 12th Streets
and Gansevoort Market Stand, inclusive.
July 28, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

724224f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - 13th Street
724224f-a.text:
Washington Street (right) at the S.E. corner of 13th Street.
April 2, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
